id: pm-xk39
title: Add audited history-stream redaction command
description: "Implement a first-class pm mutation for redacting sensitive strings from append-only history streams without hand-editing JSONL files, preserving replay integrity by recomputing affected history hashes or recording a verifiable redaction marker. Reopened because the 2026-05-09 audit still found private infrastructure paths in historical JSONL streams while current item files are mostly sanitized."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[5]: history,pm-cli,privacy,redaction,security
created_at: "2026-05-03T13:34:41.813Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-09T11:46:59.452Z"
assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-audit
acceptance_criteria: A supported pm command can redact configured literals/patterns from item files and history streams; history drift validation remains meaningful after redaction; redaction operations are themselves auditable; secret scans can include history streams without false failures from known private operations paths.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Resolution normalized from closed status; existing close_reason remains the detailed closure evidence.
expected_result: Expected closure outcome normalized from closed status; existing close_reason remains the detailed closure evidence.
actual_result: Actual closure outcome normalized from closed status; existing close_reason remains the detailed closure evidence.
